description._content: Description: Forest Guard's Station, Halefka, Kardaldagh Forest (2,400 feet above sea level) with Yiala (3,000 feet) in the background. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: View of difficult section of Halefka - Ayios Amvrossios Forest Road behind Yiala, Northern Range, Elevation 2,300 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
